# AI ButlerOS — Phase 1: Foundation

## Structure

```
ai-butleros/
├── backend/
│   ├── __init__.py
│   ├── main.py                  # FastAPI app, lifespan, event queue, routes
│   ├── core/
│   │   ├── __init__.py
│   │   └── database.py          # Async SQLAlchemy engine + get_db dep
│   ├── domain/
│   │   ├── __init__.py
│   │   └── models.py            # ExecutionTrace ORM model
│   └── services/
│       ├── __init__.py
│       └── log_service.py       # TraceService.create_trace()
├── data/                        # Auto-created; holds butler.db
└── requirements.txt
```

## Run

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt

# From repo root so `backend.*` imports resolve correctly
uvicorn backend.main:app --reload --port 8000
```

## Smoke test

```bash
curl -s -X POST http://localhost:8000/api/v1/interact \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"input": "Remind me to review the LangGraph PR tomorrow at 9am"}' | jq

# Expected:
# { "status": "queued", "trace_id": "<uuid>" }
```

Console output (within ~1 ms):
```
INFO | butleros | Event enqueued | trace_id=<uuid>
INFO | butleros | Worker picked up event | trace_id=<uuid> ...
INFO | butleros | Trace START written | trace_id=<uuid>
INFO | butleros | Trace END written   | trace_id=<uuid>
```

Two rows appear in `data/butler.db → execution_traces` with `step_name`
values `processing_started` and `processing_finished`.

## Architectural notes

| Decision | Rationale |
|---|---|
| `asyncio.Queue` (unbounded by default) | No back-pressure needed in single-user mode. Add `maxsize=` if you want to surface 503s under load. |
| Session-per-event in worker | Prevents a DB error in event N from corrupting the session for event N+1. |
| Poison-pill (`None`) for shutdown | Avoids `task.cancel()` + `CancelledError` gymnastics; graceful drain with `asyncio.wait_for` timeout. |
| `trace_id + "-start"` / `"-end"` suffix | Keeps correlating start/end pairs trivially queryable (`WHERE id LIKE '<uuid>%'`) without a separate FK column at this stage. |